        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="859"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d859">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits/9618: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-12T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 12, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>286. Your no. 402, March 3, 10 a.m. and 424, March 4, 7 p.m.<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d859fn15">Latter not printed.</note> Department appreciates progress
                    being made in program of economic and financial controls in Chile, and Embassy
                    should continue to render all proper assistance desired by Chilean Government.
                    However, such assistance should under no circumstances extend to preparation of
                    draft laws or decrees by the Embassy for consideration and possible enactment by
                    Chilean Government. Such a procedure, especially in view of del PedregaPs
                    connection with this matter, might have unfortunate repercussions. There is no
                    objection to Embassy’s making appropriate comments on decrees drafted by Chilean
                    Government or to the communication of informal and tactful oral suggestions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
